You'll hit **four obsoletion warnings** (all errors if `TreatWarningsAsErrors` is on):

| Code | API | Fix |
|------|-----|-----|
| **SYSLIB0058** | `SslStream.KeyExchangeAlgorithm`, `.CipherAlgorithm`, `.HashAlgorithm` and their `*Strength` properties | Use `SslStream.NegotiatedCipherSuite` instead. If you were validating/rejecting weak ciphers, replicate that logic against the `TlsCipherSuite` enum value. |
| **SYSLIB0059** | `SystemEvents.EventsThreadShutdown` | Replace with `AppDomain.ProcessExit`. |
| **SYSLIB0061** | `Queryable.MaxBy` overload taking `IComparer<TSource>` | Switch to the overload taking `IComparer<TKey>` (comparer over the *key*, not the source element). |
| **SYSLIB0062** | `XsltSettings.EnableScript` | XSLT embedded scripting is obsoleted with no built-in replacement. If you need script execution, suppress the warning (`#pragma warning disable SYSLIB0062`) and be aware the feature may be removed in a future release. Otherwise, move the logic out of the XSLT into C# code. |

**SYSLIB0058 migration example:**

```csharp
// Before (.NET 9)
logger.Log($"Cipher: {sslStream.CipherAlgorithm} Strength: {sslStream.CipherStrength}");

// After (.NET 10)
logger.Log($"CipherSuite: {sslStream.NegotiatedCipherSuite}");
```

**SYSLIB0059 migration example:**

```csharp
// Before
SystemEvents.EventsThreadShutdown += (s, e) => Cleanup();

// After
AppDomain.CurrentDomain.ProcessExit += (s, e) => Cleanup();
```

All four are **obsoletion warnings** (not errors by default), so the build will succeed with warnings unless you have `<TreatWarningsAsErrors>true</TreatWarningsAsErrors>`.
